social_posts.post_text: 🚨Episode 6 is LIVE 🚨 A huge thanks to @popantipop for joining us! 🙌🍻 It was a great conversation with so many gems sprinkled in for anybody to take away and apply to their own experience. 💯 Michael stop in any time, you’re always welcome on The MNO Show. 🫡

@heavenlyrecordings sent me the new album from @weareunloved in the mail, which I mixed. I got an extra little surprise inside of it. in my humble opinion this is the album of the year. Check it out when you can. @weareunloved is @xjadevincent @davidholmes_1969 and Keefus Cancia. The album features @etienne.daho @raven_violent Jarvis Cocker and Jon Spencer. It’s a splendid piece of art. A note just came up in my journal, showing me the photos of us finishing the album mixes on this day one year ago in France. It’s crazy how long releases have been pushed back due to vinyl demand. Yay vinyl!

It's pretty cool records I worked on have racked up a whopping 1.975 billion streams, 12 million Shazams, and have been heard on almost 600 million social media posts. I can't thank everyone I've met on the journey enough for their love, support, and belief in me. I'm feeling pretty #blessed today! 
As I continue to create and contribute to new projects, I can't help but think of the day when these numbers will continue to climb, reaching new heights of 10 billion streams and beyond. This may take 10-40 years, but that is the promise of streaming compared to the old-world model. And with the emergence of web3 and its potential for accurate, automated royalty collection, I'm even more excited about the future of the music industry and the ability of all people who create to share in the income generated by their work immediately without middlemen taking a cut or taking six months to pay royalties. #Web3 technology allows for a transparent and decentralized system that ensures all creators are fairly compensated for their work. It's a game changer, and I can't wait to see how it will shape the industry in the coming years. Just so you know, the #SheWantsRevenge #Shazamed #TearYouApart most Shazamed song is near and dear to my heart. It's "Tear You Apart" by She Wants Revenge.  #music #hiphop #producer #musicproducer #musicmixer #web3 #royalties #decentralization #transparency #futureofmusic" 🙏🏼🎧🔥 #studiolife #recordingartist #humblebrag" #mixingengineer @Muso.AI
What a long, strange trip it’s been, and it’s only half over. The adventure has just begun. @jaxstamusic

I'm thrilled to announce the release of the latest album from Dave Rowntree, titled "Radio Songs". As the mixer for this album, I had the privilege of working with David to bring his vision to life and I couldn't be more proud of the final product. You know him as the drummer for Blur, and this album fits very well into the legacy of the band, and their solo projects.
"Radio Songs" is a true masterpiece, with a perfect blend of eclectic and excellent tunes that are sure to keep you hooked. The album features a range of genres, from indie rock to pop, and even a hint of electronic music. David's songwriting skills are on full display, with each track showcasing his ability to craft catchy and memorable hooks.
Don't just take my word for it, check out this glowing review from Goldmine Magazine. They raved about the album's creativity and diversity, calling it "the perfect album for any music lover."
If you're a fan of great music, you won't want to miss "Radio Songs". It's available now on all the streaming platforms.

Unloved
“Polychrome” - The Pink Album Postlude
I love this album. I love The Pink Album. 
Unloved makes the coolest-sounding music you will hear today. 
David, Keefus, and Jade and geniuses of song and sound. 
I mixed both albums. 
Ahmet Ertegun, the co-founder of Atlantic Records once shared his recipe for success. 
“Walk real slow and hope you bump into a genius.” 
I am very blessed to have bumped into many, but these three humans hold a special place in my heart. 
Check out “Polychrome” and “The Pink Album” when you can. 
You will not be disappointed.

Hanging out at @thecrookedpath_la for Sit-A-Spell earlier this month. Once a month people gather there to talk about magick in an open forum led by @salvatore_modern_witch I thoroughly enjoyed the conversation and community experience. I look forward to the next one.
TBH it really bummed me out that I did not have 2 Billion streams when I posted the last version of this a couple of months ago. I feel better now. @muso.ai

I'm reminiscing about a night filled with unforgettable films and music with @kennethangerofficial and @brianbutler11 in 2016. We started off with screenings from Kenneth's "Magick Lantern Cycle" and later enjoyed a bombastic performance by Kenneth and Brian on stage. I am grateful to @lisaderrickfinearts for making the evening happen. The cultural influence of Kenneth Anger will be felt for ages. Early Cloak members will recognize what’s going on in the last photo. 🖤
When people ask me why I love living in Los Angeles I’m going to show them this photo.
